{
  "texts": [
    "The AUROCs of the LLMs on the USMLE dataset using the three different prompts are shown in Supplementary Fig. 16.",
    "It indicates that the implicit probability has a higher AUROC than that of the explicit probability under all three prompts.",
    "We also learn that the main prompt and the first prompt have similar performance in terms of AUROC for both probabilities, which is reasonable since both prompts use a similar multiplechoice format and contain similar information.",
    "The AUROC for both probabilities largely decrease when using the second auxiliary prompt.",
    "We propose that this is due to the introduction of the setting of a student proposing answers to the LLM, which introduces additional complexity and lowered the model's performance."
  ]
}